meanings: the square style of Chinese handwriting, the printed style of writing

vlive.english: Since 24, I've been doing it until now...
I cook ramen like this and kimchi...

vlive.korean: MBTI를 해서 그랬나? 컨디션 안 좋았던 게?
vlive.english: Was it because of the MBTI?
Is it because I didn't invest in Uber?

vlive.korean: 정한이 형한테 전화를 해서 하지 말아 달라고...
vlive.english: Tell him not to call me now.

examples.korean: 사장이 그를 (손짓을 해서) 자기 사무실로 불렀다.
examples.english: The boss beckoned him into her office.

examples.korean: 그 들판은 쟁기질을 해서 옥수수를 심어 놓은 상태였다.
examples.english: The field had been ploughed and planted with corn.

examples.korean: 그는 팀 동료를 비판하는, 해서는 안 될 짓을 했다.
examples.english: He committed the cardinal sin of criticizing his teammates.

examples.korean: 그녀는 터무니없는 말들을 해서 사람들에게 충격을 주는 것을 즐긴다.
examples.english: She enjoys shocking people by saying outrageous things.

examples.korean: 우리는 그가 정직하지 못해서 해고해야 했다.
examples.english: We had to fire him for dishonesty.
